Make sure these images (assets) have the size defined by TILE_SIZE (default 32x32 pixels).
# floor.xpm
# wall.xpm
# player.xpm
# collectible.xpm
# exit_closed.xpm (Exit when items remain)
# exit_open.xpm (Exit when all items collected)

Example maps/map1.ber:
11111111111
100C00000E1dmake 
10111101101
1P0C1001001
11111111111

Running the Game
MAKE, than execute the compiled program, passing the path to your map file as an argument:
# ./so_long maps/map1.ber

The game window should appear.
# Use the W, A, S, D keys to move the player.

The current move count will be printed to the terminal window where you launched the game after each valid move.
Collect all the collectibles ('C'). The exit ('E') appearance might change (if you use exit_open.xpm).
Move to the exit ('E') after collecting all items to win.
Press the ESC key or click the window's close button to quit the game.


